eventText: Mariona sent a new design draft for ESC app, on Friday 9 Feb
Philipp sent an email on Sunday, 11 Feb to program the video manager with new approach. Video manager should not be available on home screen from beginning.
Sambhaji requested on Fri, 9Feb to Ghislain to send the certificates and profiles.
Sambhaji requested Nathalie to call Ghislain on profiles, certificates
Parag discussed all the video manager options and replied back to Nathalie and Philipp at 3:01.
Sylvia sent a new feedback, which Shrinath is saying all done in the last version itself.
Sylvia and Mariona are discussing the design draft for ESC Calendar view
Parag sends an email to deactivate the tools PDF sending feature. @12Feb, 8:30 PM.
Sambhaji forwards the certificates and profiles to Shrinath. We received the profiles and certificates on @12Feb, 7:14 PM.
Nathalie is all fine with the email on video manager, sent by Parag @12Feb, 5:52PM
Philipp sends an approval for ESC app uploading @12Feb, 10:48PM
Shrinath, Piyush contacted Kapil, with downloaded guidelines details for ESC guidelines log confirmation.
Christophe sends the GL log confirmation @13Feb, 7PM
Kiran has approved the ESC app, iOS and Android from quality side. Shrinath and Piyush is uploading the iOS and Android apps resp.
Android app is online. Piyush informed the team.
ESC iOS app is approved by Apple. Sambhaji has informed all the stakeholders.
Shrinath has released the app in India only for testing purposes.
Modules team contacts Mariona and Sylvia to clear doubts on ESC Calendar design draft.
Sambhaji sent email to Ghislain, saying the developer profile is working fine. Ghislain sent the profile on @14Feb, 4:48PM.
ESC Android app, v3.7 is backed up
ESC iOS app, v3.7 is backed up
Sylvia notifies Veronica that ESC app is now online. Calendar tool, web version and windows version is still pending.
Pankaj clarifies the video manager functionality to Sylvia. Requests a Skype call.
Sylvia sends her comments on calendar tool design draft, @19Feb, 10:15PM.
Nathalie is requesting a call to discuss the multiple selection option for calendar. Nathalie is asking for efforts.
Modules team confirms to Nathalie that multiple selection fits the timeline.
Jay contacts Nathalie for outdated events. Nathalie says it's fine.
Antje sent one email for login issue for iPhoneX.
Azhar sends GIF video to Sambhaji on login. Sambhaji forwards this video to Antje.
Pranav has asked Mariona to make changes in the design draft for calendar tool.
Modules team contacts Mariona to send the calendar DD.
Mariona sends the SOP for calendar tool.
Nathalie sends screenshots of ESC home screen on iPhone10 device. Forward these screenshots to programmers.
Antje sends HCM SCD Calculator issue. HCM SCD calculator link is dysfunctional
Nathalie sends a screenshot of news tool not working properly in iPhone10 device.
Sambhaji sends the app efforts to Sylvia.
App with calendar tool is now uploaded for BBI internal testing.
Sylvia is fine with deep links for August release. Set the deadline as 25/08/2018.
Sylvia has asked for the estimations for deep links implementation.
iOS app with calendar tool is sent on testflight.
Android app is sent on testflight for Nathalie.
Sylvia contacts Lore from ESC for correct RSS feed.
Lore sends email to Sylvia, saying the RSS feed link is correct, as it doesn't make sense to show the endorsed and external events. Sambhaji sends all the changes to the team.
Veronica write that, ESC promised our National Guidelines Coordinators in December to advertise their meetings in our App. So, RSS feed may change.
Sylvia sends the screenshots to Veronica for calendar tool.
Laura says that NCS events has been added and filters should have been added.
ESC has now added non-ESC events also in the RSS feed. Sylvia can see the new events in the calendar tool.
ESC app is sent on testflight to Sylvia and Nathalie on Friday, @13April.
Sylvia has sent the feedbacks for the ESC app. Sambhaji has sent the graphics requirements.
Nilesh sends email to Christophe for guidelines logs verification.
Christophe sends the logs to Nilesh
Both iOS and Android Apps are sent on testflight for final approval from Sylvia and Nathalie.
